Another 13 luxury hotels with a total of 3,708  rooms will be built on the resort island of Bali within two years, a press  report said here Saturday.
The Bisnis Indonesia daily quoted an official with the tourism ministry,  Acep Hidayat, as saying that investment in the new hotels was estimated to  reach one trillion rupiah (464 million dollars).
Hidayat said that construction of the hotels was underway and several of  them were expected to be in operation this year and others in 1995.
The second largest tourist destination in Indonesia after Jakarta, Bali  currently has 85 star-rated hotels offering 13,717 rooms.
Indonesia expects to have 4.3 million tourists visiting the country next  year.
